<p>SMD Kozlowski (SMDK) is an autosomal dominant disorder characterized by significant scoliosis and mild metaphyseal abnormalities in the pelvis. The vertebrae exhibit platyspondyly and overfaced pedicles (Krakow et al., 2009).</p>

<p>[Krakow, D., Vriens, J., Camacho, N., Luong, P., Deixler, H., Funari, T. L., Bacino, C. A., Irons, M. B., Holm, I. A., Sadler, L., Okenfuss, E. B., Janssens, A., Voets, T., Rimoin, D. L., Lachman, R. S., Nilius, B., Cohn, D. H. Mutations in the gene encoding the calcium-permeable ion channel TRPV4 produce spondylometaphyseal dysplasia, Kozlowski type and metatropic dysplasia. Am. J. Hum. Genet. 84: 307-315, 2009.]<br/></p>